OL,3,CMuslim pilgrims warned over fake Hajj
OL,4,Ctravel packages
OL,6,FThis year, Hajj is expected to take
OL,7,Fplace between 25 May and 30 May,
OL,8,Fdepending on the sighting of the moon.
OL,10,FPilgrims are strongly advised to book
OL,11,Fonly through the official Nusuk Hajj
OL,12,FPortal and ensure their travel
OL,13,Farrangements are ATOL protected. Any
OL,14,Fpackages offered outside this official
OL,15,Fplatform`including those promoted via
OL,16,Fsocial media, messaging apps, or
OL,17,Funauthorised agents`may be fraudulent
OL,18,Fand carry significant financial risk.
OL,20,FCommon fraud techniques
